==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Detestable
<hw>De*test"a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>detestabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧testable</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Worthy of being detested; abominable; extremely hateful; very
odious; deserving abhorrence; <as>as, <ex>detestable</ex>
vices</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Thou hast defiled my sanctuary will all thy <qex>detestable</qex>
things, and with all thine abominations.</q> <rj><qau>Ezek. v.
11.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Abominable; odious; execrable;
abhorred.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Detestableness</ent>⟦br⟧
